Creating elegant, high-performance loading animations doesn�t require heavy JavaScript libraries. By leveraging CSS Keyframes and Transforms, you can build spinners that are smooth, accessible, and lightweight.

Here are 10 distinct, production-ready CSS spinners with the complete code you need to implement them immediately.

1. The Classic Dual Ring
A timeless, minimalist spinner that uses a simple border-radius and a single rotation.

<div class="dual-ring"></div>
.dual-ring {
  width: 64px;
  height: 64px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 6px solid #3498db;
  border-color: #3498db transparent #3498db transparent;
  animation: dual-ring 1.2s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes dual-ring {
  0% { transform: rotate(0deg); }
  100% { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}
